CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1958, pg. A2, reads: "Well-Equipped - Catherine Tabb, graduate model of New York's Ophelia DeFore School, obviously is well-equipped for her chosen profession of dancing. Miss Tabb, pictured bidding summer farewell at a local swimming pool, also is a member of the Phillips-Fort School of Dance to which she won a two-year scholarship. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Catherine Tabb wearing dark one piece bathing suit or leotard with belt, standing on ladder of swimming pool, at Ammon Recreation Center
